verse.lines:
{lang-eng}From heaven You came, helpless babe,
Entered our world, Your glory veiled;
Not to be served, but to serve,
And give Your life that we might live.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}There in the garden of tears,
My heavy load He chose to bear;
His heart with sorrow was torn,
“Yet not My will but Yours, “ He said.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}So let us learn how to serve,
And in our lives enthrone Him;
Each others needs to prefer,
For it is Christ we’re serving.{/lang-eng}
